1
00:00:38,420 --> 00:00:41,060
=How to Train Your Killer=

2
00:00:41,060 --> 00:00:43,900
=Episode 22=

3
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:52,710
Didn't you say
that in the martial world,

4
00:00:53,350 --> 00:00:55,520
no one's martial arts surpass yours?

5
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:57,390
Why didn't you take them down?

6
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:01,430
Look at our situation now.

7
00:01:02,350 --> 00:01:04,350
If Gu Qingyao spreads the word
about this,

8
00:01:04,590 --> 00:01:05,920
none of us will get out unscathed.

9
00:01:10,510 --> 00:01:11,790
Say something!

10
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:13,850
What on earth are we supposed to do now?

11
00:01:14,510 --> 00:01:15,760
You're too noisy.

12
00:01:24,790 --> 00:01:26,350
Now that they're cornered on all sides,

13
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:28,640
they won't dare act rashly.

14
00:01:30,150 --> 00:01:31,200
Rest easy,

15
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:35,840
everything is still within our control.

16
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,310
So you're saying,

17
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:49,070
Noble Consort Xiao tried to kill you,

18
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,790
just to take your heart's blood?

19
00:01:51,710 --> 00:01:52,550
That's right.

20
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,010
Then have you ever heard

21
00:01:54,020 --> 00:01:55,440
if there is any remedy that requires

22
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:56,980
heart's blood as the guiding ingredient?

23
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:02,400
There actually is.

24
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,000
Just a couple of days ago, I saw it.

25
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,840
It's...

26
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:08,910
It's...

27
00:02:08,910 --> 00:02:09,910
Ah, here it is.

28
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:12,170
There's a saying
in the Northern Frontier.

29
00:02:12,170 --> 00:02:15,000
Take the heart's blood
of one closest to you for medicine,

30
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:18,120
and refine it with secret arts
for 49 days.

31
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:19,960
It can trade one life for another

32
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,560
and drive away all illnesses.

33
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,800
It really can exchange life for life?

34
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,400
How could that be possible?

35
00:02:29,910 --> 00:02:31,310
I could make up a hundred

36
00:02:31,310 --> 00:02:32,840
of this kind of rumors in a day.

37
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:36,000
Why did Noble Consort Xiao

38
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,360
need your heart's blood?

39
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:40,960
I have no idea.

40
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:43,590
However, rumors in the Palace say

41
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:46,030
that the Second Prince, Ling Huan,
has been frail and sickly,

42
00:02:46,030 --> 00:02:47,130
constantly taking medicine,

43
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,990
and that with the slightest mishap,

44
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,910
he could lose his life.

45
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,630
That strange life exchange method

46
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,130
came from the Northern Frontier.

47
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,840
That guard named Wu Yun,

48
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:00,190
his martial arts don't seem
to be from the Central Plains.

49
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,240
That matches up.

50
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:03,960
It must be that guy's doing.

51
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,630
So,

52
00:03:05,630 --> 00:03:07,240
he must have used some method

53
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,280
to save Ling Huan's life.

54
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,330
That's why Noble Consort Xiao
trusts him so deeply.

55
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:15,430
But why would she want my heart's blood?

56
00:03:15,430 --> 00:03:16,680
We're not related in any way.

57
00:03:22,310 --> 00:03:23,310
I truly don't know.

58
00:03:24,110 --> 00:03:25,080
Alright, enough of that.

59
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,080
Don't look so down.

60
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,310
Do you want to hear

61
00:03:27,310 --> 00:03:28,190
some good news?

62
00:03:28,970 --> 00:03:29,810
Go on, let's hear it.

63
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,120
There's been some progress
regarding the celestial stone

64
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,590
you've been looking for.

65
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,400
A few days later

66
00:03:38,630 --> 00:03:41,080
will be the Sky Pavilion's

67
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,590
triennial Treasure Auction.

68
00:03:43,910 --> 00:03:44,840
It's said

69
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,190
there might be

70
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:48,590
a celestial stone with unknown purpose.

71
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:50,870
It could be exactly the one
you're after.

72
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:52,870
Sky Pavilion?

73
00:03:52,870 --> 00:03:53,710
Mm.

74
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:54,770
What sort of place is that?

75
00:03:54,770 --> 00:03:56,000
That's his former employer.

76
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:58,560
They deal in rare and curious treasures.

77
00:03:59,470 --> 00:04:01,360
Didn't you get thrown out

78
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,400
for stealing something?

79
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,470
Stealing? Please.

80
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:05,560
I call it borrowing.

81
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:07,400
What did you steal?

82
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:09,470
Eh, that's not important.

83
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,080
Right now, the real issue is

84
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:14,520
you need to know exactly
how much silver you have.

85
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:15,800
Without money,

86
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,270
even if you go, you can't outbid them.

87
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,560
Silver

88
00:04:23,070 --> 00:04:24,160
is a wonderful thing.

89
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,160
Ah, yes.

90
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:36,300
(Crown Prince's Residence)

91
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:48,480
20,000 taels.

92
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:50,880
Add...

93
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,630
Add...

94
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:07,950
This is 17,000 taels.

95
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,070
13,000 taels.

96
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,310
All added together,

97
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,510
my hidden stash has only
50,000 taels left.

98
00:05:32,510 --> 00:05:33,830
50,000 taels.

99
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:35,480
That should be enough, right?

100
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,160
Enough? Not even close!

101
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,630
It's not like you don't know.

102
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:44,090
Treasures in the Sky Pavilion
are worth a fortune.

103
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:46,560
How can a mere 50,000 taels be enough?

104
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:48,440
If it really comes to that,

105
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,360
go to the Crown Prince

106
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,360
and ask him for silver.

107
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:52,240
He once spent lavishly without blinking

108
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:54,000
to buy you the Ningxiang Pavilion.

109
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,480
Do you think I'm that sort of person?

110
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,320
Besides,

111
00:05:58,330 --> 00:05:59,600
I can't bring myself to ask him.

112
00:06:00,770 --> 00:06:01,710
This is all your fault.

113
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,680
You gave part of my dowry
to Shen Wanwan.

114
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,120
Otherwise,

115
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:07,190
we wouldn't be so desperate right now.

116
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:11,400
How would I know
that the prime minister's daughter

117
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,190
would be short of money?

118
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,600
I'm hardly his daughter.

119
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:25,000
It's fine.

120
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,000
What's done is done.

121
00:06:26,510 --> 00:06:27,800
We can only pray

122
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:29,160
that no one will want that stone.

123
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,000
Mm.

124
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,440
Who is it?

125
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,720
Your Highness, it's me.

126
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:44,070
Come in.

127
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:52,390
Your Highness, the Crown Prince
requests to see you.

128
00:06:52,390 --> 00:06:53,950
He says it's about an important matter.

129
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,320
Your Highness.

130
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:07,750
Qingyao, you've come.

131
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:09,870
Greetings, Your Highness.

132
00:07:10,730 --> 00:07:11,920
What do you need from me?

133
00:07:13,390 --> 00:07:14,230
Qingyao,

134
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:15,480
I've learned that your father

135
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,990
returned from Jiangnan just yesterday.

136
00:07:17,130 --> 00:07:19,600
Today, I wish to discuss with you

137
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:21,120
about his 50th birthday celebration.

138
00:07:21,950 --> 00:07:22,790
The birthday?

139
00:07:25,390 --> 00:07:26,230
What?

140
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:28,310
Qingyao, have you even forgotten

141
00:07:28,310 --> 00:07:29,290
your father's birthday?

142
00:07:30,510 --> 00:07:31,720
Of course I remember.

143
00:07:31,930 --> 00:07:33,070
Thank you for your concern.

144
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,510
I thank you on behalf of my father.

145
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,440
Now that my father is gravely ill,

146
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,390
the burden on my shoulders
has grown heavier.

147
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,800
Minister Gu has devoted himself
to the court,

148
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:47,440
and has shared much of my worries.

149
00:07:48,070 --> 00:07:50,600
I must prepare well
for this birthday banquet

150
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,160
to properly show my appreciation.

151
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:53,570
Please be at ease, Your Highness.

152
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:57,390
For my father's birthday tribute,

153
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,120
I will handle it

154
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,220
on behalf of the Residence.

155
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:01,720
It's just…

156
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,440
What is it?

157
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,680
I feel a little embarrassed
to speak of it.

158
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,440
There's no need for formality
between us.

159
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,150
If there's any difficulty,
just tell me.

160
00:08:16,920 --> 00:08:17,760
Your Highness,

161
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:22,830
my finances have been tight lately.

162
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:32,000
I thought it is something serious.

163
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:33,390
It's a simple thing.

164
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:37,390
Thank you for your kindness.

165
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,560
What is it?

166
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,770
You were thinking
of Minister Gu's birthday?

167
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:16,920
These past few days,

168
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,370
too many things have happened.

169
00:09:21,650 --> 00:09:23,180
I even forgot his birthday celebration.

170
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:27,000
You're not

171
00:09:27,510 --> 00:09:29,200
feeling guilty because of that, are you?

172
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:32,470
My father

173
00:09:34,260 --> 00:09:35,480
has always cherished me dearly.

174
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,360
The year I was born,

175
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,870
my mother passed away in childbirth.

176
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:43,910
He's treated me
like his most precious treasure,

177
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:46,360
always indulging my wishes.

178
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:49,750
But now he wants you dead.

179
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,390
Perhaps,

180
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,200
his mind has been clouded
by someone else.

181
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:01,610
It's not that he's been misled.

182
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:03,360
It's his own desire.

183
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:17,080
If you still can't let go,

184
00:10:17,390 --> 00:10:18,870
you could give him one more chance.

185
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:21,080
At this auction,

186
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:22,790
buy a treasure and gift it to him.

187
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,360
If he truly turns back,

188
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:28,390
things will be far simpler for us.

189
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,480
Shiyi.

190
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,280
Thank you.

191
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:48,580
(Sky Pavilion)

192
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,580
What's so interesting about the lanterns?

193
00:10:59,700 --> 00:11:01,820
(Sky Pavilion)

194
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,840
So this is the famed Sky Pavilion.

195
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:06,750
Quite the bold display.

196
00:11:07,550 --> 00:11:08,670
You clearly don't understand.

197
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:11,150
The trade of rare treasures

198
00:11:11,390 --> 00:11:13,240
is never a clean business.

199
00:11:14,150 --> 00:11:15,000
That's why

200
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,870
the most dangerous place

201
00:11:16,870 --> 00:11:18,390
is the safest one.

202
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:20,270
That makes sense.

203
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:23,150
Let's not waste any more time.

204
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,250
- Let's go.
- Move.

205
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:27,670
Honored guests,

206
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,060
do you have an invitation?

207
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,220
(Invitation to Sky Pavilion)

208
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:42,560
My apologies.

209
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,960
Your invitation is a forgery.

210
00:11:57,660 --> 00:12:00,260
♪When a breeze passes by♪

211
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:04,100
♪The sand and wind burn with longing♪

212
00:12:04,100 --> 00:12:06,740
♪Fearless even when thirst
goes unquenched♪

213
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:10,220
♪Like a camel wandering
with eyes closed♪

214
00:12:10,580 --> 00:12:13,540
♪When the rain quietly settles♪

215
00:12:13,540 --> 00:12:16,860
♪I think of our sorrow yet unknown♪

216
00:12:17,060 --> 00:12:19,780
♪No need to hum the song of the wind♪

217
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:23,580
♪Ignoring the sky darkening before us♪

218
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:25,340
♪I finally understood that truth♪

219
00:12:25,340 --> 00:12:26,820
♪Yet you have already faded away♪

220
00:12:27,020 --> 00:12:28,660
♪I lose my way in the night♪

221
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:30,140
♪Not knowing how to still my heart♪

222
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:31,820
♪Loving you feels like lifetimes apart♪

223
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:34,780
♪Yet longing flows back into verse♪

224
00:12:35,220 --> 00:12:37,660
♪For you and me to meet again♪

225
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:40,940
♪We must cross a thousand years
of promises♪

226
00:12:41,220 --> 00:12:43,300
♪In the pouring rain♪

227
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:47,660
♪As if you are still by my side♪
